# ZizkaDB Dashboard Conventions

## Auth
- Token: `dashboard/lib/auth.ts` — `localStorage` key `zizkadb_token`
- Dev login: `POST /v1/auth/dev-token` when `NEXT_PUBLIC_DEV_MODE=true`
- Production: OTP → `/v1/auth/request-otp`, `/verify-otp`
- All API calls: `Authorization: Bearer ${getToken()}`

## Environment
- `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL` — API base (empty = same-origin via nginx)
- `NEXT_PUBLIC_DEV_MODE` — shows "Open my dashboard" on login page
- Build: `npm ci && npm run build`
- Prod: PM2 (`dashboard/ecosystem.config.js`) or Docker (`infra/docker-compose.dashboard.yml`)

## When adding API features
- Update relevant page under `dashboard/app/dashboard/`
- Sync public docs: `dashboard/app/docs/sections.tsx`
- Match existing Tailwind patterns in `dashboard/components/`

## Pages
- `/login` — auth entry
- `/dashboard` — fleet overview
- `/dashboard/agents/[id]` — agent detail, keys, test event
- `/dashboard/search` — semantic search UI
- `/dashboard/settings` — API keys, embeddings
- `/docs`, `/trust` — marketing/technical content

## Do not
- Store API keys in localStorage (only JWT)
- Hardcode `db.zizka.ai` — use env for self-host
